Yay! ❤ Changed up the desk a bit to be more bar like height! Worked on the game engine over the weekend! Excited to do some gamedev missions. Made a few commits and removed some built in tech. I want to keep the project very lean so that it's extensible for any of my projects! I moved these out and fixed up the three examples! My game engine a game loop in javascript with some tech I've built in for responsive game view, touch/mouse input, sound, networking, surfaces, and drawing functions. It's not super complex and not even optimized very much if at all. I wrote it just to try but it just works really darn good for the projects I like to make!! :] ❤ Sometimes I like to choose exciting development over micro optimization and sometimes the other way around! It's on my github. Well most/all my projects are on my github or codepen if you ever need to look under the hood :] if you see something I make and cant find the source just message me we can find it somewhere im sure!! Anyways that is my story for tonight friend! :] .
